CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 14, 1939, pg. 9, reads: "Friday, October 27, is Charity Day for the Debs About Town in five cities: Brooklyn, New York, Boston, Washington and Pittsburgh. The local branch is having a cabaret party at Harlem Casino for its effort.  Last Sunday they met to discuss plans.  Here are pictured they heads of the various committees on their way home from the meeting.  Left to right: Eloise Robinson, emcee; Helen Douglass, hostess; Romaine Denning, prizes; Roslyn Lindsay, decorations; Ruth Buchanan, general chairman; Barbara Jones, solicitation; Alyce Lindsay, president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Debs About Town members, from left: Eloise Robinson, Helen Douglass, Romaine Denning, Roslyn Lindsay, Ruth Buchanan, Barbara Jones, and Alyce or Alice Lindsay walking up steps of Falk School, University of Pittsburgh
